            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Adding the error message to this issue so it shows up in google search for anyone else coming across this:\n\nIf you put `vim.opt.errorformat:append(\"%f:%l %m\")` this in your `init.lua` and run e.g. `nvim -q ./quickfix-list.txt` then you get a silent exit, which is a bit confusing at first.\n\nIf you set it in a running nvim instance and try to load something in to the quickfix list then you get the actual error:\n\n```\nE377: Invalid %- in format string\n```\n\nI guess the workaround is to use vimscript instead:\n\n```lua\n-- Replace\nvim.opt.errorformat:append(\"%f:%l %m\")\n\n-- With\nset errorformat+=%f:%l\\ %m\n```\n\nOr alternately you can redefine the whole list, removing anything with escaped commas, see https://github.com/gibfahn/dot/commit/43637cc135c08394e08fd9e426c328d27a162da1",
